Source: machinestate
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Reza Ebrahimi <reza.ebrahimi.dev@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 13), golang-go (>= 1.21) | golang-1.21-go
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/reza-ebrahimi/machinestate

Package: machinestate-go
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, systemd
Description: System state reporter for Linux (Go version)
 Fast, single-binary system health reporter with comprehensive
 analysis, multiple output formats, and MCP server integration.
 .
 Features:
  - Collects CPU, memory, disk, network, packages, services,
    security, hardware, Docker, Snap, GPU, and log information
  - Detects system issues with severity levels
  - Multiple output formats: terminal, JSON, HTML, Markdown
  - Continuous streaming mode with JSONL output
  - HTTP server mode with REST API and Prometheus metrics
  - MCP server integration for Claude Code
 .
 This package contains the Go implementation.

Package: machinestate-zig
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, systemd
Conflicts: machinestate-go
Description: System state reporter for Linux (Zig version)
 Fast, single-binary system health reporter with comprehensive
 analysis, multiple output formats, and MCP server integration.
 .
 Features:
  - Collects CPU, memory, disk, network, packages, services,
    security, hardware, Docker, Snap, GPU, and log information
  - Detects system issues with severity levels
  - Multiple output formats: terminal, JSON, HTML, Markdown
  - Continuous streaming mode with JSONL output
  - HTTP server mode with REST API and Prometheus metrics
  - MCP server integration for Claude Code
 .
 This package contains the Zig implementation (smaller binary).
